    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8232" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥῆγος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝρ</span>.): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">rug,
            blanket</span>, probably of wool, opp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λίνον</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 13.73</span></i>; often
          pl., mentioned as covers, cushions, for bed or chairs. (Od. and <i><span class="en">Il. 9.661</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            24.664</span></i>.) (Cf. the Assyrian and Greek <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θρόνος</span> with <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θρῆνυς</span>
          attached.) 
